A guarantor shall deliver to the first person guaranteed the following written information:
The duration of the guaranty period measured by time or, if practical, by some measure of usage such as mileage;
Any reasonable and necessary maintenance required as a condition for the performance of the guaranty;
A recital of the guarantor's obligations to the person guaranteed during the guaranty period;
The procedure which the person guaranteed should follow to obtain the repair or replacement of the malfunctioning or defective consumer product; and
Any means established by the guarantor for quick informal settlement of any guaranty dispute.

Each service contract shall be in writing and shall specify:
The duration of the service contract measured by time or, if practical, by some measure of usage;
Any reasonable and necessary maintenance required to be performed by the person guaranteed as a condition for the performance of the service contract;
The purchase price and terms of the service contract, including a recital of the provider's obligations under the service contract;
The merchandise and services to be provided;
The procedures which the person guaranteed should follow to obtain the services under the service contract or to file a claim under the service contract;
Limitations, exceptions, or exclusions, if any, under the service contract;
The terms, restrictions, or conditions governing the cancellation of the service contract before the termination or expiration date of the service contract either by the provider or person guaranteed; and
Any means established by the provider for quick informal settlement of a service contract dispute.
